34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses

37 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.

407 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
408 
409 
410 template <typename T>
411 class WeakCallbackInfo {
412  public:
413  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
414 
415  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
416  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
417  Callback* callback)
418  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
419  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
420  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
421  }
422  }
423 
424  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
425  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
426  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
427 
428  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
429  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
430  return internal_fields_[0];
431  }
432  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
433  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
434  return internal_fields_[1];
435  }
436 
437  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
438  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
439  return callback_ != nullptr;
440  }
441 
442  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
443  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
444  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
445  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
446  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
447  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
448  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
449 
450  private:
451  Isolate* isolate_;
452  T* parameter_;
453  Callback* callback_;
454  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
455 };

457 
458 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
459 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
460 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
461 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
462 // possible to request a second pass callback.
463 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

674 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
675  public:
679  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
685  template <class S>
686  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
687  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
688  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
689  }
695  template <class S, class M2>
696  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
697  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
698  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
699  }
706  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
707  Copy(that);
708  }
709  template <class S, class M2>
710  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
711  Copy(that);
712  }
713  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
714  Copy(that);
715  return *this;
716  }
717  template <class S, class M2>
718  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
719  Copy(that);
720  return *this;
721  }
727  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
728  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
729  }
730 
731  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
732  template <class S>
733  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
734 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
735  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
736  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
737  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
738 #endif
739  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
740  }
741 
742  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
743  template <class S>
744  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
745  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
746  }
747 
748  private:
749  friend class Isolate;
750  friend class Utils;
751  template<class F> friend class Local;
752  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
753  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
754 
755  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
756  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
757  template<class S, class M2>
758  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
759 };

767 template <class T>
768 class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
769  public:
773  V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
779  template <class S>
780  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
781  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
782  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
783  }
789  template <class S>
790  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
791  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
792  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
793  }
797  V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
798  other.val_ = nullptr;
799  }
800  V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
804  template <class S>
805  V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
806  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
807  if (this != &rhs) {
808  this->Reset();
809  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
810  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
811  }
812  return *this;
813  }
817  Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
818 
819  /*
820  * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
821  */
822  typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
823 
824  Global(const Global&) = delete;
825  void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
826 
827  private:
828  template <class F>
829  friend class ReturnValue;
830  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
831 };

967  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0)) {}
968  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
969  : flags_(flags & (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm)) {}
970  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
971  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
972  }
973  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
974  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
975  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
976 
977  private:
978  enum { kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1, kIsOpaque = 1 << 1, kIsWasm = 1 << 2 };
979  const int flags_;
980 };

6067 struct JitCodeEvent {
6068  enum EventType {
6069  CODE_ADDED,
6070  CODE_MOVED,
6071  CODE_REMOVED,
6072  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6073  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6074  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6075  };
6076  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6077  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6078  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6079  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6080  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6081  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6082 
6083  // Type of event.
6084  EventType type;
6085  // Start of the instructions.
6086  void* code_start;
6087  // Size of the instructions.
6088  size_t code_len;
6089  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6090  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6091  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6092  // code line information which is returned from the
6093  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6094  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6095  void* user_data;
6096

6103  };

6131 enum RAILMode {
6132  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6133  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6134  // Throughput may be throttled.
6135  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6136  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6137  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6138  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6139  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6140  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6141  // in this mode.
6142  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6143  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6144  // turn off latency optimizations.
6145  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6146 };

7719 template <class T>
7720 class Maybe {
7721  public:
7722  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
7723  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
7724 
7725  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7726  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
7727 
7728  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
7729  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
7730  return IsJust();
7731  }
7732 
7733  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7734  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
7735  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
7736  return value_;
7737  }
7738 
7739  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
7740  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
7741  }
7742 
7743  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
7744  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
7745  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
7746  }
7747 
7748  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
7749  return !operator==(other);
7750  }
7751 
7752  private:
7753  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
7754  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
7755 
7756  bool has_value_;
7757  T value_;
7758 
7759  template <class U>
7760  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
7761  template <class U>
7762  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
7763 };
7764 
7765 
7766 template <class T>
7767 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
7768  return Maybe<T>();
7769 }
7770 
7771 
7772 template <class T>
7773 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
7774  return Maybe<T>(t);
7775 }

8302 namespace internal {
8303 
8304 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8305 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8306 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8307 
8308 // Tag information for HeapObject.
8309 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8310 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8311 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8312 
8313 // Tag information for Smi.
8314 const int kSmiTag = 0;
8315 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8316 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8317 
8318 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8319 
8320 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8321 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8322  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8323  uintptr_t tagged_value =
8324  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8325  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8326 }
8327 
8328 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8329 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8330  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8331  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8332  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8333  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8334  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8335  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8336  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8337  }
8338  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8339  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8340  }
8341  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8342  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8343  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8344  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8345  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8346  //
8347  // CAUTION: The original code below:
8348  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8349  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8350  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8351  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8352  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8353  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8354  }
8355 };
8356 
8357 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8358 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8359  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8360  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8361  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8362  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8363  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8364  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8365  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8366  }
8367  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8368  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8369  }
8370  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8371  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.

8537  typedef internal::Internals I;
8538  O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);

8540  (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);

8543  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);

9020 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9021 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9022  typedef internal::Object O;
9023  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9024  typedef internal::Internals I;
9025  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9026  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9027  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9028  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9029  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9030  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9031  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9032  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9033  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9034  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9035  }
9036 #endif
9037  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9038 }
9039

9041 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9042 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9043  typedef internal::Object O;
9044  typedef internal::Internals I;
9045  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9046  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9047  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9048  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9049  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9050  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9051  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9052  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9053  }
9054 #endif
9055  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9056 }

9607  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);

9609  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
